cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI

The paper proposes a new framework for generating high-resolution character images based on structural information. This involves using progressive training to increase the resolution of both generated images and structural conditions. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves video generation and the creation of a novel dataset, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of generative adversarial networks and machine learning techniques further suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
